    • Method Detail

      • isCanceled

        boolean isCanceled()
        Allows the client an asynchronous method to cancel processing. Not all InteractiveServiceProvider implementations may support canceling; those that do may not be able to cancel immediately.
        Returns:
        true if processing should be canceled, false otherwise.

      • isProbeOnly

        boolean isProbeOnly()
        If true is returned, the InteractiveServiceProvider is instructed to only analyze the input data to see if an output may be produced. The provider will analyze the input and notify the callback via setProbeMatch(boolean) to return the probe result.
        Returns:
        true if the provider should only probe the input value, false if it should attempt to produce an output.

      • getProbeLimit

        int getProbeLimit()
        Returns the probe limit value. The interpretation of the value is specific to the class of InteractiveServiceProvider implementation. Example interpretations could be the number of bytes in a file or the number of files in a directory.
        Returns:
        The limit to be used when probing.

      • setProbeMatch

        void setProbeMatch​(boolean match)
        If isProbeOnly() returns true, the provider will invoke this method once it determines whether or not it may be able to process the input data.

        If isProbeOnly() returns false, this method will not be invoked.

        Parameters:
        match - true if the provider may be able to produce an output value for the given input value, false if no output value can be created.

      • errorOccurred

        void errorOccurred​(java.lang.String msg,
                   java.lang.Throwable t)
        This method is invoked when an error occurs during processing that will result in immediate termination with no output produced.
        Parameters:
        msg - The error message (may be null).
        t - The Throwable that was raised resulting in the termination of processing.

      • progress

        void progress​(int progress)
        This method is invoked during processing to indicate progress. The specific interpretation of the progress value is specific to the class of InteractiveServiceProvider implementation.
        Parameters:
        progress - The current progress value
